The paper deals with 3D reconstruction from RGB-D sensors, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also focuses on optimizing geometry and appearance, which falls under computer graphics (cs.GR) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of subvolumes and spherical harmonics for lighting estimation suggests a connection to multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques.
